Here's the XAML and ViewModel pattern you need:

**XAML — wrap CollectionView in RefreshView:**

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding SelectedItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="Auto,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}" WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1" Text="{Binding Name}" VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        <CollectionView.EmptyView>
            <Label Text="No items found." HorizontalOptions="Center" Margin="20" />
        </CollectionView.EmptyView>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

**ViewModel (using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm):**

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? selectedItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    public ObservableCollection<Item> Items { get; } = new();

    // Pull-to-refresh — reloads from API, then sets IsRefreshing = false
    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task RefreshAsync()
    {
        var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
        MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() =>
        {
            Items.Clear();
            foreach (var item in data)
                Items.Add(item);
        });
        IsRefreshing = false;
    }

    // Selection — navigates to detail, then clears selection
    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelectedAsync()
    {
        if (SelectedItem is null) return;

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"detail?id={SelectedItem.Id}");
        SelectedItem = null; // reset so the same item can be re-selected
    }
}
```

**Key bindings explained:**

| Property | Binding | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `IsRefreshing` | `TwoWay` (default on RefreshView) | Shows spinner; set `false` when done |
| `Command` on RefreshView | `RefreshCommand` | Triggers API reload |
| `SelectedItem` | `TwoWay` | Tracks selection; set `null` to deselect |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | `ItemSelectedCommand` | Fires navigation on tap |
| `ItemsSource` | `ObservableCollection<T>` | Auto-updates UI on add/remove |

**Important details:**
- Always use `ObservableCollection<T>`, not `List<T>`, so the UI reacts to changes.
- Set `x:DataType` on `DataTemplate` for compiled bindings.
- Reset `SelectedItem = null` after navigation so the user can re-select the same item.
- Set `IsRefreshing = false` when the refresh completes to dismiss the spinner.
- Update collections on the UI thread via `MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread`.
